ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Section F - Depression/Dysthymia. F1. In your lifetime, have you ever had at least two weeks when nearly every day you felt sad, depressed, or empty most of the time?
Notes: 1=no; 5=yes; -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused

ElementDescription: Have you ever had a time in your life lasting two weeks or more when you lost interest in most things like hobbies, work, or activities that usually give you pleasure?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: How much of the day would the worst feelings of depression usually last?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 1 = All day long; 2 = Most of the day; 3 = About half of the day; 4 = Less than half of the day

ElementDescription: Frequency of worst feelings of depression
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 1 = Every day; 2 = Almost every day; 3 = Less often

ElementDescription: Section F - Depression/Dysthymia. F12. At that time, did you lack energy or feel much more tired than usual nearly every day?  COL. I MAX SX
Notes: 1=no; 5=yes; -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused

ElementDescription: During (MOST SYMPTOMATIC PAST EPISODE), did you/she lose or gain weight without trying?
Notes: No = 0; Yes = 1; -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 2 = Lost; 3 = Both gained and lost weight; 4 = Stayed about the same or on a diet; 5 = Gained

ElementDescription: Amount of weight gained (lbs)
Amount of weight lost (lbs)
Did you have more trouble falling asleep than you usually do?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: How often did you have more trouble falling asleep than usual?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 1 = Every night; 2 = Nearly every night; 3 = Less often

ElementDescription: Section F - Depression/Dysthymia. F18. Nearly every day did you have a lot more trouble concentrating than is normal for you?  COL. I MAX SX
Notes: 1=no; 5=yes; -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused

ElementDescription: People sometimes feel down on themselves, no good, or worthless. Did you feel this way?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Did you think a lot about death - either your own, someone else's, or death in general?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: About how many weeks altogether were the feelings of depression or loss of interest the worst? Include the weeks before, during, and after the worst two weeks.
Notes: Number of weeks

ElementDescription: How many periods in your life were the feelings of depression or loss of interest the worst?
Notes: Number of periods

ElementDescription: About how old were you the FIRST time you had a period of two weeks when the feelings of depression or loss of interest the worst? Include this period whether or not you received any help for it.
Notes: Years of age when the feelings of depression or loss of interest were the worst (first episode)

ElementDescription: About how old were you the LAST time you had a period of two weeks when the feelings of depression or loss of interest were the worst? Include this period whether or not you received any help for it.
Notes: Years of age when the most recent episode happened

ElementDescription: Did you ever tell a professional about these major depressive symptoms (medical doctor, psychologist, social worker, counselor, nurse, clergy, or other helping professional)?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Did you take medication or use drugs or alcohol more than once for these major depressive symptoms?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: How much did these major depressive symptoms interfere with your life or activities?
Notes: -2 = Not Asked; -1 = Refused; 1 = A lot; 2 = Some; 3 = A little; 4 = Not at all

ElementDescription: Probability of caseness for DSM-IV Major Depression
QIDS Sleep onset insomnia
Notes: 0=Never takes longer than 30 minutes to fall asleep; 1=Takes at least 30 minutes to fall asleep less than half the time; 2=Takes at least 30 minutes to fall asleep more than half the time; 3=Takes more than 60 minutes to fall asleep more than half the time; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Mid-nocturnal insomnia
Notes: 0=Does not wake up at night; 1=Restless light sleep with few awakenings; 2=Wakes up at least once a night but goes back to sleep easily; 3=Awakens more than once a night and stays awake for 20 minutes or more more than half the time; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: In the past 7 days, which of these responses most accurately describes your Waking Up Too Early:
Notes: 0 = Most of the time, I awaken no more than 30 minutes before I need to get up. ; 1 = More than half the time, I awaken more than 30 minutes before I need to get up. ; 2 = I almost always awaken at least one hour or so before I need to, but I go back to sleep eventually. ; 3 = I awaken at least one hour before I need to, and cannot go back to sleep. ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Hypersomnia
Notes: 0=Sleeps no longer than 7-8 hours per night without naps; 1=Sleeps no longer than 10 hours in a 24 hour period including naps; 2=Sleeps no longer than 12 hours in a 24 hour period including naps; 3=Sleeps longer than 12 hours in a 24 hour period including naps; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Mood (sad)
Notes: 0=Does not feel sad; 1=Feels sad less than half the time; 2=Feels sad more than half the time; 3=Feels intensely sad virtually all of the time; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Appetite (decreased)
Notes: 0=No change from usual appetite; 1=Eats somewhat less often and/or lesser amounts than usual; 2=Eats much less than usual and only with personal effort; 3=Eats rarely within a 24 hour period and only with extreme personal effort or with persuasion by others; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Appetite (increased)
Notes: 0=No change from usual appetite; 1=More frequently feels a need to eat than usual; 2=Regularly eats more often and/or greater amounts than usual; 3=Feels driven to overeat at and between meals; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Weight (decrease) last 2 weeks
Notes: 0=Has experienced no weight change; 1=Feels as if some slight weight loss has occurred; 2=Has lost 2 pounds or more; 3=Has lost 5 pounds or more; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Weight (increase) last 2 weeks
Notes: 0=Has experienced no weight change; 1=Feels as if some slight weight gain has occurred; 2=Has gained 2 pounds or more; 3=Has gained 5 pounds or more; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Concentration/decision making
Notes: 0=No change in usual capacity to concentrate and decide; 1=Occasionally feels indecisive or notes that attention often wanders; 2=Most of the time struggles to focus attention or make decisions; 3=Cannot concentrate well enough to read or cannot make even minor decisions; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Outlook (self)
Notes: 0=Sees self as equally worthwhile and deserving as others; 1=Is more self blaming than usual; 2=Largely believes that he/she causes problems for others; 3=Ruminates over major and minor defects in self ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Suicidal ideation
Notes: 0=Does not think of suicide or death; 1=Feels life is empty or is not worth living; 2=Thinks of suicide/death several times a week for several minutes; 3=Thinks of suicide/death several times a day in depth or has made specific plans or attempted suicide ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Involvement
Notes: 0=No change from usual level of interest in other people and activities; 1=Notices a reduction in former interests/activities; 2=Finds only one or two former interests remain; 3=Has virtually no interest in formerly pursued activities ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Energy/fatigability
Notes: 0=No change in usual level of energy; 1=Tires more easily than usual; 2=Makes significant personal effort to maintain usual daily activities; 3=Unable to carry out most of usual daily activities due to lack of energy ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Psychomotor slowing
Notes: 0=Normal speed of thinking/gesturing/speaking; 1=Patient notes slowed thinking and voice modulation is reduced; 2=Takes several seconds to respond to most questions and reports slowed thinking; 3=Is largely unresponsive to most questions without strong encouragement ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: QIDS Psychomotor agitation
Notes: 0=No increased speed or disorganization in thinking or gesturing; 1=Fidgets and wrings hands and shifts positions often; 2=Describes impulse to move about and displays motor restlessness; 3=Unable to stay seated and paces about with or without permission ; 999 = Prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: Total score of all 16 PhenX Adult Depression items that come from QIDS
Total score of the 16 items from part II PhenX Dep
Notes: Total score is obtained by adding highest score from phenx_dep_1-phenx_dep_4, the individual score for item phenx_dep_5 (sad mood), the highest score from items phenx_dep_6-phenx_dep-9, the individual scores from items phenx_dep_10-phenx_dep14 and the highest score from items phenx_dep_15-phenx_dep_16
